The case is active, but not yet determined to be a threat. Requires constant attention.
The case is active but not being proactively pursued.
The case is active and determined to represent a threat . Requires total commitment of effort to monitor, track, and status.
The case is active of sufficient interest to maintain on a watch list.

The case has been closed.
The case in no longer of interest, but a decision to close the case has not been made.

The case has been created, but will not become active until triggered by a date-time, event, or user action.
The case is no longer active, but can be returned to an active state by a time or event trigger, or user action.
The case status is unknown.

General risk that the case represents activities or items intended to support a terrorist attack.

High risk that the case represents activities or items intended to support a terrorist attack.

Low risk that the case represents activities or items intended to support a terrorist attack.
The case represents activities or items that have been adjudicated by the governing authority to not represent a threat of terrorist attack.
Severe risk that the case represents activities or items intended to support a terrorist attack.
Significant risk that the case represents activities or items intended to support a terrorist attack.
The threat represented by the activities or items is unknown.

A data type that defines the FacilityCategoryCodes
A facility where aircraft arrive and depart.
A facility that engages in rad/nuc detection enounters with respect to vehicles and rail transport.
A facility involved with responding to identified rad/nuc threat materials.
A facility where vessels arrive and depart.
A facility that supports the rad/nuc detection/interdiction mission but does not directly engage in detection encounters.
A facility involved in fusion and situation awareness monitoring of rad/nuc detection/interdiction activities.
A data type for the categories of facilities.
A data type that defines the Facility Operational Status Codes
The site has been decommissioned and is not longer available to support the mission.
The site is mission ready, but has been degraded and is not at full capability.
The site is in the process of being physically implemented.
The site is fully mission capable to include communications networks.
The site is not capable of supporting its assigned mission.
The site is not in existence. It represents a planned site at some point in the future.
The status of the site is unknown.
A data type for the operational states of a facility or site.
A data type to describe the uses of real property facilities.
A facility within an educational facility for the collection, storage and retrieval of print, audio and visual materials.

A building containing general office space as well as space typically associated with office space. Associated space may include conference rooms, small storage rooms, restrooms, break/lunch rooms, locker/shower rooms, and utility rooms.
A facility that houses any administrative services of a government.
A facility that houses the administrative services of a military.
Miscellaneous administrative structures such as flagpoles, billboards, reviewing stands, and information stands.

An underground facility containing general office space as well as that space typically associated with office space. Associated space may include conference rooms, small storage rooms, restrooms, break/lunch rooms, locker/shower rooms, and utility rooms.
Terminals for the movement of people and goods from one location to another via air travel.
A single building containing multiple dwellings that limits occupants to a specific age range.
A facility that utilizes different aspects of farming to produce a profit.

A facility for conducting public sales in which agricultural commodities such as grain, fruits, or livestock are sold to the highest bidder. Facility may include storage space for livestock and other commodities.
Facilities specializing in horticulture, agriculture or the production of living things.
A facility for maintaining and working on machinery specifically used for agriculture.
Buildings used directly in theoretical or applied research, development, testing, and evaluation activities for agricultural sciences.
Agricultural Research Facility

A facility for the education of adults on the subjects of crop production, livestock management, soil and water conservation and other area of agriculture in the attempt of earning a terminal degree in a related field.
A facility for the storage of plants, animals and other agriculture specific items.
Land specifically zoned or reserved for the agricultural purposes or the building of agriculture facilities.
A facility for the housing and/or organization of storage containers transported by airplane.

ownedLiteral.name: Aircraft Research Development Test and Evaluation Facility

ownedComment.body: Buildings used in the direct research, development, testing, and evaluation of airframes and other related assemblies, spares, and aircraft equipment.
An area provided for aircraft parking, servicing, and loading.

A facility, in a separate building or combined with a flight control tower or fire and rescue station and used to administer operations, possibly including spaces for meeting, communications, transient waiting, and briefing pilots.
A thoroughfare, route, or path reserved for use by planes and other aircraft.
A thoroughfare, route, or path reserved for the landing and taking off of planes.
A thoroughfare, route, or path connecting a runway to and apron or storage facility.
A military facility specific to the Air Force.
A facility for the repair of aircraft and supply necessary fluids and fuel.
An enclosed, reinforced facility, generally within or beneath an existing building, that provides protection against air attack and/or nuclear fallout.
A narrow lane found in urban areas which usually runs between or behind buildings.
A facility that provides short term lodging through individual living dwellings containing sleeping quarters, living areas and typically kitchens or cooking areas.

A facility supporting the communication and computer services for the National Command Authority, the Joint Staff, OSD, and other DoD Agencies and functions as a disaster recovery site. It is capable of housing the Emergency Operations Centers for the Military Departments. This FAC will only be used by WHS.
A detached facility to protect ambulances from the elements.
A health care facilities for surgical procedures not requiring an overnight hospital stay are performed.

ownedLiteral.name: Ammunition, Explosive, and Toxic Research Development Test and Evaluation Facility

ownedComment.body: Buildings used in the direct research, development, testing, and evaluation of ammunition, explosives, and toxic materials.

ownedLiteral.name: Ammunition, Explosives, and Toxic Maintenance Facility

ownedComment.body: A facility used by a military for the upkeep and maintenance of ammunition, explosives and toxic materials.

ownedLiteral.name: Ammunition, Explosives, and Toxics Production Facility

ownedComment.body: A facility for the creation of ammunition and other explosives.
An indoor facility containing multiple video games and/or other small amusement games such as skee-ball, air hockey and foosball.
Facility for operating and supporting the feeding of livestock; may be integrated into a livestock facility, or separately located.

A facility for administrative and operational functions of veterinary activities assigned to the installation. These can include animal medical care, control of communicable animal diseases, animal boarding, and food inspection.
A facility that offers short term lodging for animals.
Facilities for the support of recreational pursuits involving animals.
A facility for the collection and storage of animal waste and by-product.
Land specifically zoned or reserved for the building of apartments.
A facility that specializes in the raising of bees for the production of honey, honey comb and/or wax.
A facility that specializes in the raising of fish, crustaceans and other aquatic creatures or plants.
A facility for the conveyance and delivery of water.

A sports arena, usually oval or horseshoe-shaped, with tiers of seats for spectators. Interior sports area usually contains a field for football, soccer, baseball, softball, or track and field events.
A military facility specific to the Army or Marine Corps.
A high-capacity urban road.
A facility for the exhibition of art, usually visual art.
A facility for the education of adults on the subject of art in the attempt of earning a Bachelor of Arts (B.A.) or a Master of Arts ( M.A.).
Facilities where large groups of individuals can gather and assemble for commercial, entertainment, educational, and other purposes.
A facility where goods and products are sold to the highest bidder.
Auditoriums and theaters provide space for administrative areas, seating and viewing, film projection and storage, live performances, concession stand, toilets, lobby and ticket sales.
A facility that sells automotive goods through auction.
A facility for the repair of automobiles and filling of necessary fluids and fuel.

A building or part of a building that contains the equipment and functions of automated data processing. Equipment located in these facilities is not real property and is not included in this Facility Analysis Category.
A facility that provide space for auto bays, administration, classroom, tool storage and checkout, break area and lavatories.
A facility for the temporary housing of automobiles.
A facility for the controlled racing of automobiles (often modified cars, trucks or motorcycles).
A facility that provides the following essential services: checking and savings accounts, loans, foreign currency sales, etc.
A facility for short term lodging often located within a residence and offers breakfast as part of the accommodations.
A dwelling containing multiple sleeping quarters typically with shared eating, living and lavatory facilities and staffed with medical workers that specialize in caring for the mentally ill.
A road that encircles a town or city.

ownedLiteral.name: Beverage and Tobacco Manufacturing Research Development Test and Evaluation Facility

ownedComment.body: Building used in the direct research, development, testing, and evaluation of soft drink, ice, and bottled water manufacturing; breweries; wineries; distilleries; and tobacco stemming, redrying, and product manufacturing.
A facility for the creation of beverages or tobacco products.
A facility specializing in a single (or select few) merchandising needs that offers an extreme selection of products.
An indoor facility containing multiple pool tables and seating.

Facilities used for clinical, diagnostic, teaching, research, or production work that is performed with indigenous or exotic agents with a potential for respiratory transmission, and which may cause serious and/or potentially lethal infection applicable to Risk Group 3 pathogenic agents as defined by the latest edition of Biosafety in Microbiological and Biomedical Laboratories, U.S. Department of Health and Human Services, Public Health Service, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, and National Institutes of Health.
A facility for the storage and maintenance of small boats and canoes.

ownedLiteral.name: Boat Maintenance and Fueling Dry Docks

ownedComment.body: A facility for the repair of marine equipment on land and supply necessary fluids and fuel.
An indoor facility containing multiple bowling lanes and seating.
An indoor facility containing a boxing ring (or multiple boxing rings) as well as medicine ball, speed ball and punching bag stations for boxers to train and/or fight.
A structure built to span physical obstacles such as a body of water, valley, or road, for the purpose of providing passage over the obstacle.

A building containing the equipment and functions that provide photographic or television production. Equipment located in these facilities is not real property and is not included in this Facility Analysis Category.
The acquisition and/or improvement of a building. This Facility Analysis Category should not be used for inventory purposes.
A facility for the storage of bulk liquid fuels.
A facility for the storage of bulk liquids, other than fuels.
A collection of office buildings grouped closely to form a neighborhood of tenants.
A facility for the education of adults on the subject of business and economics in the attempt of earning a degree in Business Administration (BA) and/or Masters of Business Administration (MBA).
A facility for individuals to await bus service.
A man-made facility for the navigation of waterways or channeling of water.

A facility for raising and lowering traffic between stretches of water of different levels on river and canal waterways. The distinguishing feature of a lock is a fixed chamber whose water level can be varied.
A facility for the housing of goods to be shipped.
A facility which houses and accommodates gambling activities.
A facility that offers short term lodging and is connected to or is part of a casino complex.
A facility for the creation of construction and decorative rock and cement products.
Those areas set aside for burial of the dead.
A facility that provides space for the molding, forming and firing of ceramic products.
A facility for the indoor conduct of ceremonies during inclement weather.

A publicly funded facility that has been freed from some of the rules, regulations, and statutes that apply to other public schools, in exchange for some type of accountability for producing certain results, which are set forth within the school's charter.
A facility for the creation of chemicals products.

ownedLiteral.name: Chemical Manufacturing Research Development Test and Evaluation Facility

ownedComment.body: Building used in the direct research, development, testing, and evaluation of chemicals, including petrochemical; industrial gas; synthetic fibers/filaments; pesticides, fertilizers, and other agricultural chemicals; pharmaceuticals; paint, coating, and adhesives; soap and cleaning compounds; et al.
Buildings used directly in theoretical or applied research, development, testing, and evaluation activities for chemistry research.
A facility for the collection, storage and retrieval of print, audio and visual materials specifically suited to children and young adults.
A facility for the exhibition of world issues and history with the intent of making the topics easily understood for children through mostly experiential activities.

ownedLiteral.name: Chilled Water and Refrigerant Distribution Line

ownedComment.body: Pipelines for the transport of water or other coolants between a central cooling plant and the facilities to be cooled.
A facility that is capable of lowering the temperature of water.
A facility for the display and viewing of motion pictures/movies/films.
The removal of vegetation, reshaping of the land surface, and/or the planting of decorative trees and shrubs. This Facility Analysis Category should not be used for inventory purposes.
A health care facility that is primarily devoted to the care of outpatients.
A facility for the sales of military clothing and personal equipment.

A facility for use by active duty military personnel, authorized civilians, and their family members for private organization/club meetings and activities that are not affiliated with the US government.
A facility for the generation of electrical power by either burning coal to create steam to turn turbines, or by burning coal to power a generator.
Land that touches or is surrounded by a body of water.
A military facility specific to the Coast Guard.
Multiple dwellings that share facilities (typically kitchen, dining, laundry and recreational areas are shared).
A facility for the storage of goods that require to be held below a certain temperature to prevent spoiling.
Roads that provide service to and between traffic generators such as larger towns or consolidated schools, commercial or industrial areas, or serve as links between arterial roadways and highways.
A structure for the placement and storage of cinerary urns. Columbaria can be either integrated into an interior or boundary wall, or part of a mausoleum or another building.
A facility that offers a wide variety of retail stores for consumers in addition to other services such as dining.
A structure for docking ships that extends into the waterway such that ships can dock along both sides.
Land specifically zoned or reserved for the development of commercial facilities.
A health care facility that specializes in the consultation, treatment or advanced medical procedures delivered on an outpatient basis.

ownedLiteral.name: Computer and Electronic Product Manufacturing Research Development Test and Evaluation Facility

ownedComment.body: Buildings used in the direct research, development, testing, and evaluation of computer and peripheral equipment manufacturing; communications equipment manufacturing; audio/video equipment manufacturing; semiconductor and other electronic component manufacturing; navigational, measuring, electromedical, and control instruments manufacturing;
A facility for the production, quality assurance, and calibration of electronic and communication equipment and components.
A facility used to house large collections of computers or very large, single computers capable of vast computing operations.
Buildings used directly in theoretical or applied research, development, testing, and evaluation activities for computational research.
A room or hall where individuals of differing sized groups can meet for a singular event or meeting either in person or via audio and/or video conferencing system.
Land that offered for preservation purposes between a landowner and a government agency.
A facility for the housing of goods intended for direct sale to individual consumers.

A facility or land that has been contaminated and in unavailable for use, excluding as impact areas. This Facility Analysis Category should not be used for inventory purposes as the facility or land is also captured in other categories.
Land that is not suitable for use due to the presence of hazardous waste.
A facility that offers a wide range of readily used items but with limited selection.
A collection of retail facilities in one building but with separate entrances from the outside and parking.
A facility, typically large in scale, designed to hold a convention, exhibition, conference or group of individuals gathered to promote and share a common interest.
A facility with sufficient floor area to accommodate several thousand individuals in addition to multiple display areas and booths.
A facility that offers short term lodging and is connected to or is part of a convention center.
Any public road maintained by the county in which it originates or resides. The term is common and almost always designates major roads.
A facility that houses both a local court of law and occasionally the regional government.
A facility for the housing of goods that must be protected from natural elements such as sun or rain.
A facility that provide space for administration, drawing and art studio, storage, photo dark room, audio/photo sales area, separate areas for individual crafts and arts, and kiln area for ceramics.
A facility that provides space for the weaving, cutting, dying and assemble of fabric products.
A facility that offers office/production space with little or no interior structure to inhibit tenants use of the space.
A facility that provides cremation services for the deceased and their families.
A facility that produces large quantities of grain or other plant based foods as the major source of income.
Facilities used for programs or activities focused on the arts, personal beliefs or other activities focused on personal growth and reflection.

The removal of soil from higher elevations and/or the placement of soil in lower elevations to prepare a site for further construction. This Facility Analysis Category should not be used for inventory purposes.
A facility that specializes in the harvesting of animal milk.

A barrier constructed to obstruct the normal flow of a watercourse. This FAC includes all civil works dams and other water collecting facilities, whether man-made or natural, together with appurtenant water diversion, regulation and delivery facilities and spillways, outlet works, and power intake works.
A facility for the care and education of infants thru pre-school age children and for school aged children less than 12 years of age before and after normal public school hours.
A facility for the care and education of children by a person other than the child's guardian or immediate family.
A facility, either detached or within a hospital, for the identification, preparation, and holding of human remains.
The razing of structures and other obstructions and subsequent removal of debris. This Facility Analysis Category should not be used for inventory purposes.
A facility that provides routine and specialized dental treatment to authorized personnel. Classified as a Business Occupancy facility under the NFPA Life Safety Code.

A facility that sells a wide range of the consumer's personal and residential product needs; and at the same time offering the consumer a choice of multiple manufactures, in a wide range of product categories.
An covered storage area to be used for depot-level storage.
An open storage area to be used for depot-level storage. Usually a paved surface.

A facility to house and secure service members during pre-trial confinement, post-trial confinement, and for the duration of sentences. Although not normally housed in the same facility, prisoners can include officers, enlisted personnel, and prisoners of war. Functional space includes sleeping space, administrative areas, dining areas, recreational and educational areas, vocational areas, and health clinics.
Facilities that provide delivery, distribution and/or sale of prepared food and drink.
A facility which sells both food and beverages and contains both an open floor space for dancing and an audio booth or stage to allow for musical performances.
A facility for the collection and organization of storage containers for transportation.
A facility for the controlled racing of canines.
A single building containing multiple sleeping quarters and typically shared eating and lavatory facilities typically for students.
The removal of the bed material underlying a body of water, to provide operating channels, maneuvering area, anchorages and moving basins for ships.
A connection between a public roadway and a residence, business or destination.
Facilities for the collection and housing of goods that are either dry by nature or need to remain dry.
A two dwelling apartment or condominium.
Land specifically zoned or reserved for the building of duplexes or small, multi-family residences.
Facilities designed for instruction of students and research accompanying higher education.
A dwelling containing multiple sleeping quarters with shared eating, living and lavatory facilities and staffed with medical workers that specialize in care of older patients.

ownedLiteral.name: Electrical Equipment, Appliance, and Component Manufacturing Research Development Test and Evaluatio

ownedComment.body: Buildings used in the direct research, development, testing, and evaluation of electrical lighting equipment manufacturing, household appliance manufacturing, battery manufacturing, communication and energy wire and cable manufacturing, wiring device manufacturing, and electrical equipment manufacturing.

ownedLiteral.name: Electrical Equipment or Appliance Manufacturing Facility

ownedComment.body: A facility for the creation of electronics and appliance goods.
Facility for the housing of electrical current.

Equipment to step down the voltage of the electric power supply before it enters the distribution network, normally consisting of incoming power lines (higher voltage), transformers to convert the incoming voltage, switchgear to distribute the converted power, and necessary safety and security equipment. This category does not include a building to house the equipment (see FAC 8910 Utility Building).

Equipment used to distribute the incoming electric power supply as required to provide electrical service to separate areas and/or facilities. The switching station has no transformers but otherwise is similar to a substation. The switching station consists of switchgear and all necessary safety and security equipment but does not include a building to house the equipment (see FAC 8910 Utility Building).

Equipment used to convert the supplied power voltage before transmitting it further in the electrical distribution network. Transformers may be pole-mounted, pad-mounted, or housed in a building. This CATCODE does not include a building to house the equipment (see FAC 8910 Utility Building) or the pad on which the equipment may be mounted (see FAC 8526 Miscellaneous Paved Area).
A facility, other than a building, designed to support electronic and communication equipment maintenance, repair, and inspection activities. Cost factors based on an average size of 5,500 SF.
A facility designed to house electronic and communication equipment maintenance, repair, and inspection activities.

ownedLiteral.name: Electronic and Communication Maintenance Shop, Depot

ownedComment.body: A facility designed to house electronic and communication equipment maintenance, repair, and inspection activities at the depot level.

ownedLiteral.name: Electronics and Communications Equipment Maintenance Facility

ownedComment.body: Facilities designed to allow for maintenance, repair, and inspection of electronics and communication equipment.
Buildings used directly in theoretical or applied research, development, testing, and evaluation activities for electrical research.
A facility generally outfitted or intended for use in providing children with the earliest stages of education.

A facility (residence or office) that serves as the permanent diplomatic mission of a state or inter-governmental organization present in another state for purposes of representation and diplomatic endeavors.

A facility such as hutments that can be used for emergency housing during training, mobilization, deployments, and natural disasters. These facilities provide bare minimum shelter that does not meet the criteria for permanent housing.
Facilities for the transfer of energy or fuels.
Facilities for the dispensing of energy and/or the conversion of fuel into a new form of energy.
Facilities and structures for the production, management and distribution of energy utilities, including but not limited to gas and other fuels, and electrical power.
A plant for the generation of electrical power.
Facilities for the housing of energy sources and fuels.

Building used directly in theoretical or applied research, development, testing, and evaluation activities for engineering science including all engineering disciplines, applied sciences, and applied mathematics.
Buildings used directly in theoretical or applied research, development, testing, and evaluation activities for engineering research.
Facilities used to house an entertainment act or activity.
Facilities specializing in the production of entertainment content.
A facility separate from performance facility used for the purpose of rehearsal and practice of musical and theatrical performances.
A facility for the housing of goods that require specific environment conditions.
A facility for the housing of machinery needed for the production or maintenance of other goods.
Tent pads, which can be used for erecting tents for emergency housing during training, mobilization, deployments, and natural disasters. Cost factors are based on the area of a GP Medium tent.
A facility where goods, products, commodities and securities are traded or sold.
Administrative or maintenance facilities that support exchange operations.
Storage facilities that support exchange operations.
A facility that houses or offers the ability to safely practice explosive and flame weapon basics.
A rail yard used for the transfer and/or temporary holding of ammunition and explosive materials.
A facility for the housing of explosives.

Outdoor lighting such as street lights and perimeter lights. This FAC should only consist of pole-mounted lighting, not luminaries mounted on buildings or luminaries mounted on electrical distribution poles.
A facility for atmospheric and space aircraft flight operations to take place, regardless of whether they involve cargo, passengers or neither.
A facility for the creation of fabricated metal products and goods.
A temporary facility containing multiple entertainment venues, rides and attractions for then entertainment of crowds.
A trailer or movable dwelling unit for a service member or for an authorized government civilian and his/her authorized dependents when accompanied by those dependents.
Pads or sites with associated utilities provided for privately or government owned trailers and mobile homes.
A facility to provide a responsive source of information, guidance, and assistance in solving problems of a personal nature to military personnel and their dependents.
A facility that specializes in the rapid production and distribution of food with minimal table service.
Land comprising the whole or a part of a military installation that is owned by the Federal Government.
An often open-air facility for the feeding of livestock with grain and feed.
Facilities containing or distributing water for the purpose of limiting or preventing fire.
